Business Brief -- Ford Motor Co.:
   Recall on a Brake Problem
   Slated for 517,600 Trucks
The vehicles involved include certain 1988-1991 model-year
F-250 and F-350 trucks, that have over 8,500 pounds gross
vehicle weight rating. Ford said it won't begin the recall
until late next month, when it will have the parts needed to
make the repairs.
   In separate actions, Ford is recalling 500 1992 model-year
Taurus and Sable station wagons, and 2,200 1992 Thunderbird
and Cougar cars equipped with 3.8-liter engines, to fix
separate, minor problems.